metadata.description:
1) Reconstruction of paleoclimate and paleoenvironment from Ordovician carbon and oxygen isotope data in Bachukeping area, Tarim Basin;
2) The data comes from Ordovician limestone samples in Bachu and Keping areas of the Tarim Basin, mainly in the Middle Late Ordovician, and powder samples are obtained through micro drilling and micro grinding sampling;
3) The samples were mainly tested at the Stable Isotope Laboratory of Ruhr University Bochum in Germany, and the data quality was stable and reliable;
4) The data obtained was published in PPP in 2023, and it has certain reference value for the restoration of Ordovician paleoclimate and paleoenvironment, especially since these data are based on different carbonate compositions and are more refined than previous sampling methods.
